Hypertension and other risk factors in peripheral arterial disease. Aim of this study has been to evaluate the prevalence of arterial hypertension and other risk factors in patients suffering with PAD in two clinical samples (1.: 102 patients with PAD, 69 M, 33 F, studied in our angiology laboratory, matched for sex and age with 102 healthy volunteers 2.: 184 hospitalized patients, 80 M, 104 F, mean age 57.2 +/- 10.8, with PAD) and in two epidemiological studies (1.: Trabia Study, 835 subjects